<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-08-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-08-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="1414" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1414">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/758.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Special Agent <persName type="to">Carothers</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-13">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 13, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Tlahualilo Company reports: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Villa decree is worse than, reported, 10 per cent of invoice
                                    value and 7 per cent of cotton produced must be delivered in
                                    bales to cuartel general.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>Continue earnest efforts for repeal of this decree.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>